<Author>BurtonsCurtains
<Content>Great location The Hotel Pierre in Florence is great. It's a 4 star I think, and lived up to what I expect from a 4 star hotel. I thought the price was ok too, considering Florence is fairly expensive, as it's an in-demand tourist destination. The location is perfect - everything we wanted to see in Florence, we walked to from there. And I had a bad back and my mum a bad hip at the time. The ponte vecchio, uffizi, duomo etc are all probably less than 5 mins walk away. Designer shop heaven is even closer. There is also a fairly nice restaurant right over the road, open til about 11.30pm.The room was spacious (we had a superior, they also do standard and deluxe, but we checked them out and not much difference, just a few square feet either way), clean and comfortable. There was also hot water and no drainy smell, which is what I had read about other hotels, in travellers' reviews. Staff are nice and helpful, speak good english. The view from the room was rubbish - a wall, but this is very similar with lots of hotels in Florence. It's built up and street views can be noisy, so this was better, on reflection. The continental breakfast was ok, not amazing, but better than a lot I had read about before travelling. I would definitely stay there again (and I usually go 5 star, so that's good). 
