<Content>Quite nice hotel in a great city This is a nice hotel. Our rooms were large, bathrooms fine, staff nice and helpful, corridors a bit bizarre - two buildings joined, so strange doors to open and lock every time you left room. Breakfast best eaten elsewhere. But the big point is the location. It's near everything and everything you want or need is just a walk away.So having agreed that the hotel is adequate, let's deal with the really important thing - enjoying Florence!A few suggestions to take or leave. Eat at Il Latini - 6 via dei Palchetti, Trattoria 4 Leoni - 1 via dei Vellutini. Both welcoming and seriously good food and wine. Have lunch at the Yellow Bar - 39 via Proconsolo - good fun, pizza and other dishes, informal.Buy a hat from Borsalino - via della Vigna Nuova (round corner from hotel). Buy a tie from Piero Puliti - 51 via del Corso. Look at bags at Bisonte - via Rapine (?). Get a bus or taxi to Fiesole for lunch, go for a walk and look back over Florence. Terrific.One caution. If you have a room at the back of the hotel, there are markets across the road which set up around 6 am. They'll wake you up, so you might want to ask for a front or side room.Enjoy! 
