<Author>ChoosyTravelers
<Content>Amazing Location, Bad breakfast As many others have written the location of the hotel is truly amazing. It is in the heart of Florence no further than a 5 minute walk to the Duomo and Uffizi as well as the Ponte Vecchio. Spent 2 nights there in connecting rooms for a family of 4. The rooms were spacious and well airconditioned. Bathrooms very nice although as others have noted small showers. . . Make sure to reserve tickets to the Uffizi and the Accademia before you go . . . there are many services that charge high fees, but make sure that you book thru the central booking service as their fees were nominal. Take the audio tour at the Uffizi.Breakfast was the worst of 4 hotels that we stayed at in Italy -- it shouldn't be that hard to serve a solid continental breakfast with good breads, fresh fruit and accompaniments, but the Hotel Pierre hasn't figured that out yet. Stay at the hotel, but find a delicious patisserie to start your day.Dinner recommendation, which I hate to share, but it's really that good -- Il Quattro Leoni -- ate their both nights. Service and food excellent. Go after 8:30 and it's a good mix of both tourists and locals. You might be waiting for a table outside for a long time if you don't reserve ahead of time.Il Santo Bevitore also had great menu, but probably not a great restaurant for those travelling with kids. 
