<Author>prospero1b
<Content>Best Location in Town Spent four nights at the Pierre on holiday with family.This hotel has probably the best location of any quality hotel in Florence; it is bang in the centre of the action, a two minute walk from the Piazza della Signoria and the Uffizi, surrounded by restaurants and very close to world-class shopping.It is a small hotel, very clean and well decorated. We had a deluxe room, with a view over the street, which is virtually pedestrianised. Furniture was uncluttered and tasteful. Bathroom very good quality, with marble and chrome fittings, towelling bathrobes and slippers. The staff are friendly without being over-familiar, very happy to help with any request. There is no restaurant, which is not a problem, because there are dozens of superb restaurants within easy walking distance. There is a pleasant breakfast room, serving a decent continental breakfast.A couple of comments on earlier reports: first, there most certainly is air conditioning in the bedrooms. We stayed in a heatwave and the bedroom was beautifully cool.Secondly, there will of course be some street noise. This is, after all, the centre of a major European tourist city. However, this is not intrusive, particularly if you close the heavy wooden shutters, which exclude most of the street noise at night.This hotel cannot be beaten in Florence. Its location alone makes it special, but there is more to it than that. I have given it a 5 rating, because it is outstanding in its category and excellent value. I will certainly stay here again next time I am in Florence. 
