<Author>Bay_Area_Traveler62
<Content>Good Location, Nice Place I stayed at the Hotel Pierre June 26-30 with 8 others in my group. Overall this is a clean, comfortable hotel located close to the Uffizi, Duomo, Ponte Vecchio (all that you came to see in Florence). Only a 10 minute walk to the train station. Shopping galore (mainly expensive, except for marketplace area), many places to eat. Try ZaZa's for a fun  festive dining experience. Gelato is easily found all around the hotel. The lobby and little corner bar area are nice, clean, inviting. The front desk is somewhat helpful, but sometimes appear too busy to help you. We had no hot water our last morning. Other than that, the rooms were very clean, great beds, lovely thick towels, pretty marble bathroom. As others have noted, the shower stall IS small, so beware. No tub, but there is a bidet. Only English speaking station on the tv is CNN (fyi). The breakfast downstairs is served in a lovely room with nicely set tables and dishes, but the food is mediocre. The melon and pineapple were the best things. Pastry was below average (although kept in a warming bin - why bother?), powdered eggs and little hot dog sausages were not very good at all. Dry melba toast (cracker) is served in a package, and there is yogurt, cereals, salame, cheese, etc. An ok breakfast. Tons of jam, honey and nutella, but nothing to really spread it on but dry rolls. Our rooms were quiet, well kept, comfy. As I said, super walking location to all attractions, clean, pleasant. I'd give it a solid 3.5 stars out of 5.0 stars. 
