<Content>Location, Location, Location!!! What a great location! My mother and I stayed at the Hotel Pierre in December as part of a working trip for me. It was right in the middle of everything, in an easy walking distance to everything. The Ufizzi, the Duomo, Ponte Vechio, great restaurants, really everything. When we got in we had just arrived from a flight from the US, then the train ride, we were exhausted and hungry and Lucia was an angel. She actually walked us to two nearby restaurants and talked to the people there to have them help us a little before their normal serving time, so, we could get to bed. She also booked us with the best tour guide at the Ufizzi gallery as we had forgotten that the weekend we were there was a bank holiday and was quite crowded. We were worried a bit as the first stop on our tour had no line whatsoever, but, it worked out great, and we just had an absolutely fabulous weekend. They really were all about customer service and soooo friendly. It could have been an act, but, really seemed sincere. Where in America will someone walk you anywhere to do you a favor? Not too many places!The rooms were bigger than others I've had in Italy with a spacious bathroom and in the inside, very quiet and pleasant. In addition, when we called for our American coffee in the mornings it was there in less than 5 minutes. A great start to our days. The breakfast was ok, the typical Italian hotel staples, yogurt, granola, cappucino, but, a fine start nonetheless. The streets were all decorated for Christmas and lit up at night, it was quite something, a memory forever. Thanks Hotel Pierre! 
