<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>GREAT HOTEL !!! Following the good reviews on tripadvisor I wanted to book 6 nights for August 19-26 2004.The prices mentionned are much more than what you can get it for: 99 euros on hotels or 120 on the hotel Pierre website directly for a double for 2 people. Given the fact that Florence is expensive and that this is a 4 star located right in the center (2 min walk from Duomo, Palazzio Vecchio, etc.) and with breakfast this is unbeatable to me.Add to that a big well lit nicely decorated palazzio room with american queen sized bed, parquet floor, carpets, satellite TV (Olympics on eurosport uk!), full marble bathroom with hairdryer, bath, bidet, massive mirror and bathrobes.Breakfast is composed of croissants (chocolate or cream stuffed and unstuffed), italian rice cake, butterbread or complete rolls, french toast, cereals, fruit salad, fruits, nutella, jams, scrambled eggs, sausages, hams, cheese, hot/cold milk, tea, coffee, orange, grapefruit and pineapple juice (from concentrate) !For lunch and dinner you get from trattorie on the way to the sites 4 euros pizze or pasta and 1.5 euro italian ice cream easily.Central location is great for sightseeing (everything to see is really in the center not spread all over in Florence (less than 10 min walk to any site)) or shopping (all major shops around (Furla, Diesel, Fendi, etc.)). Friendly and efficient staff.Finally, as my first name is Pierre, this hotel was meant for me and I highly recommend it. 
